Peggy Joan Trawick, age 73|http://thecitizen.com|https://thecitizen.com/2018/10/10/peggy-joan-trawick-age-73/|Obituary|2018-10-10|Stranger Than Fiction||Peggy Joan Trawick, 73, of Hampton passed away October 6, 2018. She was born in Mobile, Alabama on March 22, 1945 to the late George and Audenese Spurlock.

Peggy was preceded in death by her husband, Bernard Andy “Butch” Trawick in 2016, two brothers, George Spurlock, Jr. and Robert Spurlock and her parents. She is survived by her son, B. Andy Trawick, Jr. of Atlanta; daughters. Tammy (Jeff) Kirby of Stockbridge and Robin Dickinson of Ellenwood; grandchildren, Brandie Kirby of Stockbridge, Noah Kirby of Stockbridge, and MaKiya Dickinson of Ellenwood; great-grandson, Rowen Kirby of Stockbridge; and brothers, Bobby Lee Brantley and Ronnie Harold Brantley of Warner Robins.

A memorial service will be held at 3 p.m. on Saturday, October 20, 2018 at Fayetteville Church of Christ, 870 Redwine Road, Fayetteville, Georgia 30215 (770) 461-3617. The family will receive friends from 2-3 p.m. prior to the service at the church. In lieu of flowers, the family asks that donations in memory of Joann Trawick be made online at www.crosswalkusa.org or mailed to Crosswalk Ministries, P. O. Box 1613, McDonough, GA 30253,

Carl J. Mowell & Son Funeral Home, Fayetteville – www.mowellfuneralhome.com
